Value: zygote

Subject: 4-cell stage
Value: Four cell-stage embryo. Second cleaveages unipolar and start at the animal pole (about 80-110 min post fertilization at 18 degree celsius).

Subject: very early gastrula stage
Value: Visible pointed oral pole but no cell ingression, ciliogenesis starting (12-13h post fertilization at 18 degree celsius).

Subject: 4-bulb medusa stage
Value: period of medusa growth between release medusa from gonozoid  until appearance of secondary tentacles. Only  4 tentacle bulbs present

Subject: 8-bulb medusa stage
Value: period of medusa growth when only 8 tentacles are present

Subject: 12-bulb medusa stage
Value: period of medusa growth when only 12 tentacles are present

Subject: 16-bulb immature medusa stage
Value: period of medusa growth when only 16 tentacles are present. No mature gametes (eg 5mm diameter)

Subject: early blastula
Value: Blastula stage embryo before epithelisation.

Subject: mid gastrula
Value: Gastrula in which blastotocoel is half filled with ingressing cells.

Subject: gametogenesis period
Value: phase of sexual reproduction in which certain cells of a female or male individual (parent) are transformed into specialized reproductive cells (gametes) that will initiate development of a progeny individual (offspring) upon fertilization.

Subject: oocyte meiotic maturation
Value: oocyte undergoing meiosis completion from prophase I to G0  of first meiotic cycle

Subject: unfertilized egg stage
Value: matture female germ cell. not yet fertilized. Meiotic divisions complete. Spawned egg with female pronucleus.

Subject: spermatozoid stage
Value: mature male germ cell.

Subject: 32-cell stage
Value: thirty two cell-stage embryo (about 3h post fertilization at 18 degree celsius).

Subject: 64-cell stage
Value: sixty four cell-stage embryo (about 3h post fertilization at 18 degree celsius).

Subject: settled planula stage
Value: torpedo shape planula that stopped swimming

Subject: blob stage
Value: irregularly shaped metamorphosing planula attached to substrate, not yet flattened

Subject: disc stage
Value: metamorphosing planula attached to the substrate and in shape of a flattened disc

Subject: sculpted disc stage
Value: metamorphosing planula attached to the substrate and in shape of a flattened disc with sculpted indentations

Subject: primary polyp stalk extension stage
Value: uniform extension emerging from the sculpted disc

Subject: primary polyp developing head stage
Value: swollen distal extremity developing into a functional primary polyp head

Subject: functional primary polyp stage
Value: theca of the primary polyp open on the oral side and mouth open

Subject: colony phase
Value: colony containing  mature or developing gonozoids , gastrozoids and stolons.

Subject: stalk extenstion stage
Value: uniform extension emerging from the stolon as first stage of gastrozoid development

Subject: developing head stage
Value: swollen distal extremity developing into a complete gastrozoid head

Subject: functional gastrozoid stage
Value: complete and functional gastrozoid with open hydrotheca and mouth

Subject: growing gonozoid stage
Value: growing and developing gonozoid

Subject: budding gonozoid stage
Value: mature gonozoid budding medusae

Subject: non-budding gonozoid stage
Value: mature gonozoid not containing any medusa bud only central tube and disc-shaped cap

Subject: early medusa bud stage
Value: medusa bud with visible ectoderm, endoderm and entocodon

Subject: mid medusa bud stage
Value: medusa bud with forming subumbrella cavity

Subject: late medusa bud stage
Value: medusa bud with with folding umbrella

Subject: 4-bulb medusa stage
Value: period of medusa growth between release medusa from gonozoid  until appearance of secondary tentacles. Only  4 tentacle bulbs present

Subject: 8-bulb medusa stage
Value: period of medusa growth when only 8 tentacles are present

Subject: 12-bulb medusa stage
Value: period of medusa growth when only 12 tentacles are present

Subject: 16-bulb immature medusa stage
Value: period of medusa growth when only 16 tentacles are present. No mature gametes (eg 5mm diameter)

Subject: mature adult medusa stage
Value: period of medusa growth when only 16 tentacles are present. Gonads contain mature gametes. (eg 10mm diameter)
